<L>__{exterior the porch, nolan house, new orleans night, 1925}
<A>__{a line of old people in rockers. benjamin, like any six year old, bored, wheels his chair back and forth, between them... until one of the oldsters, who has had enough, sticks his cane in the spokes of his wheelchair, making him come to an abrupt stop... benjamin, sitting with the other oldsters on the porch... the old people rocking... sounds drift from the street beyond the wall... children playing... people talking...}
<C>__{benjamin button}
<D>__{what's there?}
<A>__{nobody says anything, rocking. benjamin, eternally curious needing to know, suddenly wheels himself precariously to the very edge of the porch where the wall is lower and he just sees the street... children running on the street, playing... carriages dropping people off for a party... he leans forward to get an even better view... when queenie suddenly grabs him...}
<C>__{queenie}
<D>__{benjamin! that's dangerous... come back here...!}
<A>__{...rolling his wheelchair away from the edge to the safety of the old people... out of sight of the street...}
